deck: Brun is a tunneler.
description:
Origin

Brun is a member of a species of tunnelers. They build their tunnels a 1,000 feet down, where the temperature is higher. The resin in their saliva hardens in the heat, keeping walls from caving in.

It was revealed by Felicia Book that Brun was pregnant.

Powers & Abilities

Brun can fortify stones with his saliva. The silicate in his saliva smells of cherries.

His skin hardens when it's heated.

His species grow their offspring in their fingers.

description:
Origin

Recca was the son of the leader of the Hokage Clan during the 16th century in Japan. He was born with the potential to control and manipulate fire, an ability that manifested in future leaders of the Clan.

The Hokage Ninja's were wiped out when Recca was a baby, and to protect him his Mother used her magical powers to send him forward in time 400 years just as the enemy were about to close in.

Recca grew up on the present day with no knowledge of his heritage.

Creation

Recca is the main protagonist of the series "Flame of Recca", he was created by Nobuyuki Anzai for Shogakukan's Japanese anthology comic, Weekly Shonen Sunday.
name: Recca Hanabishi

deck: Luna is an Inhuman girl with a genius-level intellect who befriends Devil Dinosaur.
description:
Origin

Lunella is a young girl living in America. She seemed just a regular young girl, but actually is part of an ancient race known as the Inhumans and she is one of the smartest people on the planet!

Creation

Lunella Lafayette (Moon Girl) was created by Amy Reeder-Hadley, Brandon Montclare and Natacha Bustos and first appeared in Moon Girl and Devil Dinosaur issue 1 (2016).

Major Story Arcs

Befriending a Dinosaur

Luna noticed on a very early age that she was smarter then most people. While her parents tried to help her find changlenges for her intellect, she was soon borred in her school-class, but managed to make some friends while there.

It was then that Luna noticed a strange connection between her and a giant red Dinosaur named Devil Dinosaur that appeared suddenly.

Other Media

Games

Marvel Future Fight

Moon Girl is a playable character in the game. She is a blast type.

Her bio in the game says: Through just a small child, Lunella Lafayette is the smartest person on Earth. As a human and Inhuman hybrid, Luna possesses vast intelligence and a knack for inventing strange gadgets. After creating her latest invention, the Omni-Wave Projector, Luna opens a portal to Dinosaur World and befriends the monstrous Devil Dinosaur, who aids her in her adventures. Exposure to the Terrigen Mist strengthens the bond between Luna and Devil Dinosaur, as her latent Inhuman powers allow her to swap consciousness with the gigantic beast.

Marvel Avengers Academy

Moon Girl is a playable character in the game. She was introduced during the "Monsters Unleashed Event". Her recruitment quest is Get Moon Girl!.

deck: Nadeen Hassan is a young teenager rescued by the Howling Commandos after she lost control of her abilities to summon ancient spirits.
description:
Nadeen Hassan was a teenager who had become a beacon that summoned ancient Egyptian spirits. She couldn't control her powers, and accidentally caused the disappearance of a train in the New York Subway.

The Howling Commandos of S.H.I.E.L.D. were sent to investigate, and encountered Nadeen, who warned them of her inability to seize her ability. Vampire by Night managed to enter in Nadeen's subconscious and help her get hold of the spirits, vanishing them.

Nadeen was brought in by Commander Dum-Dum Dugan to Area 13 in order to help her control her abilities. While she still grieved for her predicament, Nadeen befriended the other teenager in Area 13, who was imprisoned next to her, Jamie Carlson, the Teen Abomination.

While she was having a dream about her twin brother Navid, this scenario turned into a nightmare and Nadeen found herself without control of her own body. Navid had possessed her body, in a similar way as he did when Nadeen was in the subway, and stormed Area 13 with Egyptian spirits. After Jamie was forced to knock her down, Nadeen recovered and revealed that when Navid was in her mind, she was able to peek into his, and find out the Howling Commandos were in grave danger.

Due to the chaos she had unwillingly wreaked at the S.T.A.K.E. HQs, Nadeen was imprisoned and tortured in order to learn who did she supposedly work for. After returning from his mission, Dugan was notified of Nadeen's condition and freed her against his superior's will. Dugan welcomed Nadeen as a full-fledged member of the Howling Commandos, and together with the rest of the team, she traveled to New York City to stop the rampage of Navid and his mentor, the Sphinx, in Grandview Museum.

During the ensuing fight, Nadeen discovered that her brother had been possessed by the Adversary, who soon started to change Navid's body to his own image. Using the Mask of Amenhotep, the powerful item the Sphinx and Nadeen were trying to acquire, the Commandos cast the Adversary away, but killing Navid in the process. While her brother died, Nadeen was glad she had finally started getting comfortable with her powers, and had found a place in the world with the Howling Commandos.
name: Glyph

deck: A villainous Inhuman who wishes to evolve every human genetically so they are as powerful as him, but under his control.
description: The Shredded Man was originally a man named Ivan Guerrero. He found out that he had cancer in his lungs. He was cursed by the Terrigen Mist when he isolated himself and his granddaughter Emily Guerrero within a cacoon, becoming a Inhuman. Afterwards he traveled around the world for months but everywhere he went he would see the worst of humanity, making him develop a hatred for humans. Becoming the Shredded Man, he now tries to take over the world but is prevented from doing so by Cable and Synapse.
